436inline bool isInvalidData(double value) {
437 return qIsNaN(value) || qIsInf(value);
438}
439
445inline bool isInvalidData(double value1, double value2) {
446 return isInvalidData(value1) || isInvalidData(value2);
447}
448
455inline void setMarginValue(QMargins &margins, QCP::MarginSide side, int value) {
456 switch (side) {
457 case QCP::msLeft:
458 margins.setLeft(value);
459 break;
460 case QCP::msRight:
461 margins.setRight(value);
462 break;
463 case QCP::msTop:
464 margins.setTop(value);
465 break;
466 case QCP::msBottom:
467 margins.setBottom(value);
468 break;
469 case QCP::msAll:
470 margins = QMargins(value, value, value, value);
471 break;
472 default:
473 break;
474 }
475}
476
484inline int getMarginValue(const QMargins &margins, QCP::MarginSide side) {
485 switch (side) {
486 case QCP::msLeft:
487 return margins.left();
488 case QCP::msRight:
489 return margins.right();
490 case QCP::msTop:
491 return margins.top();
492 case QCP::msBottom:
493 return margins.bottom();
494 default:
495 break;
496 }
497 return 0;
498}

513class QCP_LIB_DECL QCPVector2D {
514 public:
515 QCPVector2D();
516 QCPVector2D(double x, double y);
517 QCPVector2D(const QPoint &point);
518 QCPVector2D(const QPointF &point);
519
520 // getters:
521 double x() const { return mX; }
522 double y() const { return mY; }
523 double &rx() { return mX; }
524 double &ry() { return mY; }
525
526 // setters:
527 void setX(double x) { mX = x; }
528 void setY(double y) { mY = y; }
529
530 // non-virtual methods:
531 double length() const { return qSqrt(mX * mX + mY * mY); }
532 double lengthSquared() const { return mX * mX + mY * mY; }
533 double angle() const { return qAtan2(mY, mX); }
534 QPoint toPoint() const { return QPoint(int(mX), int(mY)); }
535 QPointF toPointF() const { return QPointF(mX, mY); }
536
537 bool isNull() const { return qIsNull(mX) && qIsNull(mY); }
538 void normalize();
539 QCPVector2D normalized() const;
540 QCPVector2D perpendicular() const { return QCPVector2D(-mY, mX); }
541 double dot(const QCPVector2D &vec) const { return mX * vec.mX + mY * vec.mY; }
542 double distanceSquaredToLine(const QCPVector2D &start,
543 const QCPVector2D &end) const;
544 double distanceSquaredToLine(const QLineF &line) const;
545 double distanceToStraightLine(const QCPVector2D &base,
546 const QCPVector2D &direction) const;
547
548 QCPVector2D &operator*=(double factor);
549 QCPVector2D &operator/=(double divisor);
550 QCPVector2D &operator+=(const QCPVector2D &vector);
551 QCPVector2D &operator-=(const QCPVector2D &vector);
552
553 private:
554 // property members:
555 double mX, mY;
556
557 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator*(double factor,
558 const QCPVector2D &vec);
559 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator*(const QCPVector2D &vec,
560 double factor);
561 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator/(const QCPVector2D &vec,
562 double divisor);
563 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator+(const QCPVector2D &vec1,
564 const QCPVector2D &vec2);
565 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec1,
566 const QCPVector2D &vec2);
567 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec);
568};
569Q_DECLARE_TYPEINFO(QCPVector2D, Q_MOVABLE_TYPE);
570
571inline const QCPVector2D operator*(double factor, const QCPVector2D &vec) {
572 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX * factor, vec.mY * factor);
573}
574inline const QCPVector2D operator*(const QCPVector2D &vec, double factor) {
575 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX * factor, vec.mY * factor);
576}
577inline const QCPVector2D operator/(const QCPVector2D &vec, double divisor) {
578 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX / divisor, vec.mY / divisor);
579}
580inline const QCPVector2D operator+(const QCPVector2D &vec1,
581 const QCPVector2D &vec2) {
582 return QCPVector2D(vec1.mX + vec2.mX, vec1.mY + vec2.mY);
583}
584inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec1,
585 const QCPVector2D &vec2) {
586 return QCPVector2D(vec1.mX - vec2.mX, vec1.mY - vec2.mY);
587}
588inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec) {
589 return QCPVector2D(-vec.mX, -vec.mY);
590}
591
596inline QDebug operator<<(QDebug d, const QCPVector2D &vec) {
597 d.nospace() << "QCPVector2D(" << vec.x() << ", " << vec.y() << ")";
598 return d.space();
599}

936class QCP_LIB_DECL QCPRange {
937 public:
938 double lower, upper;
939
940 QCPRange();
941 QCPRange(double lower, double upper);
942
943 bool operator==(const QCPRange &other) const {
944 return lower == other.lower && upper == other.upper;
945 }
946 bool operator!=(const QCPRange &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
947
948 QCPRange &operator+=(const double &value) {
949 lower += value;
950 upper += value;
951 return *this;
952 }
953 QCPRange &operator-=(const double &value) {
954 lower -= value;
955 upper -= value;
956 return *this;
957 }
958 QCPRange &operator*=(const double &value) {
959 lower *= value;
960 upper *= value;
961 return *this;
962 }
963 QCPRange &operator/=(const double &value) {
964 lower /= value;
965 upper /= value;
966 return *this;
967 }
968 friend inline const QCPRange operator+(const QCPRange &, double);
969 friend inline const QCPRange operator+(double, const QCPRange &);
970 friend inline const QCPRange operator-(const QCPRange &range, double value);
971 friend inline const QCPRange operator*(const QCPRange &range, double value);
972 friend inline const QCPRange operator*(double value, const QCPRange &range);
973 friend inline const QCPRange operator/(const QCPRange &range, double value);
974
975 double size() const { return upper - lower; }
976 double center() const { return (upper + lower) * 0.5; }
977 void normalize() {
978 if (lower > upper) qSwap(lower, upper);
979 }
980 void expand(const QCPRange &otherRange);
981 void expand(double includeCoord);
982 QCPRange expanded(const QCPRange &otherRange) const;
983 QCPRange expanded(double includeCoord) const;
984 QCPRange bounded(double lowerBound, double upperBound) const;
985 QCPRange sanitizedForLogScale() const;
986 QCPRange sanitizedForLinScale() const;
987 bool contains(double value) const { return value >= lower && value <= upper; }
988
989 static bool validRange(double lower, double upper);
990 static bool validRange(const QCPRange &range);
991 static const double minRange;
992 static const double maxRange;
993};

2929template <class DataType>
2930inline bool qcpLessThanSortKey(const DataType &a, const DataType &b) {
2931 return a.sortKey() < b.sortKey();
2932}

3152template <class DataType>
3153QCPDataContainer<DataType>::QCPDataContainer()
3154 : mAutoSqueeze(true), mPreallocSize(0), mPreallocIteration(0) {}

3164template <class DataType>
3165void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::setAutoSqueeze(bool enabled) {
3166 if (mAutoSqueeze != enabled) {
3167 mAutoSqueeze = enabled;
3168 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();

3178template <class DataType>
3179void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::set(const QCPDataContainer<DataType> &data) {
3180 clear();
3181 add(data);
3182}
3183
3194template <class DataType>
3195void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::set(const QVector<DataType> &data,
3196 bool alreadySorted) {
3197 mData = data;
3198 mPreallocSize = 0;
3199 mPreallocIteration = 0;
3200 if (!alreadySorted) sort();
3201}
3202
3209template <class DataType>
3210void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const QCPDataContainer<DataType> &data) {
3211 if (data.isEmpty()) return;
3212
3213 const int n = data.size();
3214 const int oldSize = size();
3215
3216 if (oldSize > 0 &&
3217 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3218 *constBegin(),
3219 *(data.constEnd() - 1))) // prepend if new data keys are all smaller
3220 // than or equal to existing ones
3221 {
3222 if (mPreallocSize < n) preallocateGrow(n);
3223 mPreallocSize -= n;
3224 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), begin());
3225 } else // don't need to prepend, so append and merge if necessary
3226 {
3227 mData.resize(mData.size() + n);
3228 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), end() - n);
3229 if (oldSize > 0 &&
3230 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3231 *(constEnd() - n - 1),
3232 *(constEnd() - n))) // if appended range keys aren't all greater
3233 // than existing ones, merge the two partitions
3234 std::inplace_merge(begin(), end() - n, end(),
3235 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3236 }
3237}
3238
3248template <class DataType>
3249void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const QVector<DataType> &data,
3250 bool alreadySorted) {
3251 if (data.isEmpty()) return;
3252 if (isEmpty()) {
3253 set(data, alreadySorted);
3254 return;
3255 }
3256
3257 const int n = data.size();
3258 const int oldSize = size();
3259
3260 if (alreadySorted && oldSize > 0 &&
3261 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3262 *constBegin(), *(data.constEnd() -
3263 1))) // prepend if new data is sorted and keys are
3264 // all smaller than or equal to existing ones
3265 {
3266 if (mPreallocSize < n) preallocateGrow(n);
3267 mPreallocSize -= n;
3268 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), begin());
3269 } else // don't need to prepend, so append and then sort and merge if
3270 // necessary
3271 {
3272 mData.resize(mData.size() + n);
3273 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), end() - n);
3274 if (!alreadySorted) // sort appended subrange if it wasn't already sorted
3275 std::sort(end() - n, end(), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3276 if (oldSize > 0 &&
3277 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3278 *(constEnd() - n - 1),
3279 *(constEnd() - n))) // if appended range keys aren't all greater
3280 // than existing ones, merge the two partitions
3281 std::inplace_merge(begin(), end() - n, end(),
3282 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3283 }
3284}
3285
3292template <class DataType>
3293void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const DataType &data) {
3294 if (isEmpty() ||
3295 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3296 data, *(constEnd() - 1))) // quickly handle appends if new data key
3297 // is greater or equal to existing ones
3298 {
3299 mData.append(data);
3300 } else if (qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3301 data, *constBegin())) // quickly handle prepends using
3302 // preallocated space
3303 {
3304 if (mPreallocSize < 1) preallocateGrow(1);
3305 --mPreallocSize;
3306 *begin() = data;
3307 } else // handle inserts, maintaining sorted keys
3308 {
3309 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator insertionPoint =
3310 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), data, qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3311 mData.insert(insertionPoint, data);
3312 }
3313}
3314
3320template <class DataType>
3321void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::removeBefore(double sortKey) {
3322 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it = begin();
3323 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd =
3324 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3325 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3326 mPreallocSize +=
3327 int(itEnd -
3328 it); // don't actually delete, just add it to the preallocated block
3329 // (if it gets too large, squeeze will take care of it)
3330 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3331}
3332
3338template <class DataType>
3339void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::removeAfter(double sortKey) {
3340 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it =
3341 std::upper_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3342 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3343 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd = end();
3344 mData.erase(it, itEnd); // typically adds it to the postallocated block
3345 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3346}
3347
3356template <class DataType>
3357void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::remove(double sortKeyFrom, double sortKeyTo) {
3358 if (sortKeyFrom >= sortKeyTo || isEmpty()) return;
3359
3360 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it =
3361 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKeyFrom),
3362 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3363 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd =
3364 std::upper_bound(it, end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKeyTo),
3365 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3366 mData.erase(it, itEnd);
3367 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3368}
3369
3379template <class DataType>
3380void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::remove(double sortKey) {
3381 QCPDataContainer::iterator it =
3382 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3383 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3384 if (it != end() && it->sortKey() == sortKey) {
3385 if (it == begin())
3386 ++mPreallocSize; // don't actually delete, just add it to the
3387 // preallocated block (if it gets too large, squeeze
3388 // will take care of it)
3389 else
3390 mData.erase(it);
3391 }
3392 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3393}

3400template <class DataType>
3401void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::clear() {
3402 mData.clear();
3403 mPreallocIteration = 0;
3404 mPreallocSize = 0;
3405}
3406
3419template <class DataType>
3420void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::sort() {
3421 std::sort(begin(), end(), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3422}
3423
3435template <class DataType>
3436void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::squeeze(bool preAllocation,
3437 bool postAllocation) {
3438 if (preAllocation) {
3439 if (mPreallocSize > 0) {
3440 std::copy(begin(), end(), mData.begin());
3441 mData.resize(size());
3442 mPreallocSize = 0;
3443 }
3444 mPreallocIteration = 0;
3445 }
3446 if (postAllocation) mData.squeeze();
3447}

3465template <class DataType>
3466typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator
3467QCPDataContainer<DataType>::findBegin(double sortKey,
3468 bool expandedRange) const {
3469 if (isEmpty()) return constEnd();
3470
3471 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it =
3472 std::lower_bound(constBegin(), constEnd(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3473 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3474 if (expandedRange &&
3475 it != constBegin()) // also covers it == constEnd case, and we know
3476 // --constEnd is valid because mData isn't empty
3477 --it;
3478 return it;
3479}
3480
3498template <class DataType>
3499typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator
3500QCPDataContainer<DataType>::findEnd(double sortKey, bool expandedRange) const {
3501 if (isEmpty()) return constEnd();
3502
3503 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it =
3504 std::upper_bound(constBegin(), constEnd(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3505 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3506 if (expandedRange && it != constEnd()) ++it;
3507 return it;
3508}
3509
3526template <class DataType>
3527QCPRange QCPDataContainer<DataType>::keyRange(bool &foundRange,
3528 QCP::SignDomain signDomain) {
3529 if (isEmpty()) {
3530 foundRange = false;
3531 return QCPRange();
3532 }
3533 QCPRange range;
3534 bool haveLower = false;
3535 bool haveUpper = false;
3536 double current;
3537
3538 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = constBegin();
3539 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itEnd = constEnd();
3540 if (signDomain == QCP::sdBoth) // range may be anywhere
3541 {
3542 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // if DataType is sorted by main key
3543 // (e.g. QCPGraph, but not QCPCurve), use
3544 // faster algorithm by finding just first
3545 // and last key with non-NaN value
3546 {
3547 while (it != itEnd) // find first non-nan going up from left
3548 {
3549 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3550 range.lower = it->mainKey();
3551 haveLower = true;
3552 break;
3553 }
3554 ++it;
3555 }
3556 it = itEnd;
3557 while (it != constBegin()) // find first non-nan going down from right
3558 {
3559 --it;
3560 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3561 range.upper = it->mainKey();
3562 haveUpper = true;
3563 break;
3564 }
3565 }
3566 } else // DataType is not sorted by main key, go through all data points
3567 // and accordingly expand range
3568 {
3569 while (it != itEnd) {
3570 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3571 current = it->mainKey();
3572 if (current < range.lower || !haveLower) {
3573 range.lower = current;
3574 haveLower = true;
3575 }
3576 if (current > range.upper || !haveUpper) {
3577 range.upper = current;
3578 haveUpper = true;
3579 }
3580 }
3581 ++it;
3582 }
3583 }
3584 } else if (signDomain ==
3585 QCP::sdNegative) // range may only be in the negative sign domain
3586 {
3587 while (it != itEnd) {
3588 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3589 current = it->mainKey();
3590 if ((current < range.lower || !haveLower) && current < 0) {
3591 range.lower = current;
3592 haveLower = true;
3593 }
3594 if ((current > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current < 0) {
3595 range.upper = current;
3596 haveUpper = true;
3597 }
3598 }
3599 ++it;
3600 }
3601 } else if (signDomain ==
3602 QCP::sdPositive) // range may only be in the positive sign domain
3603 {
3604 while (it != itEnd) {
3605 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3606 current = it->mainKey();
3607 if ((current < range.lower || !haveLower) && current > 0) {
3608 range.lower = current;
3609 haveLower = true;
3610 }
3611 if ((current > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current > 0) {
3612 range.upper = current;
3613 haveUpper = true;
3614 }
3615 }
3616 ++it;
3617 }
3618 }
3619
3620 foundRange = haveLower && haveUpper;
3621 return range;
3622}
3623
3642template <class DataType>
3643QCPRange QCPDataContainer<DataType>::valueRange(bool &foundRange,
3644 QCP::SignDomain signDomain,
3645 const QCPRange &inKeyRange) {
3646 if (isEmpty()) {
3647 foundRange = false;
3648 return QCPRange();
3649 }
3650 QCPRange range;
3651 const bool restrictKeyRange = inKeyRange != QCPRange();
3652 bool haveLower = false;
3653 bool haveUpper = false;
3654 QCPRange current;
3655 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itBegin = constBegin();
3656 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itEnd = constEnd();
3657 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey() && restrictKeyRange) {
3658 itBegin = findBegin(inKeyRange.lower, false);
3659 itEnd = findEnd(inKeyRange.upper, false);
3660 }
3661 if (signDomain == QCP::sdBoth) // range may be anywhere
3662 {
3663 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd;
3664 ++it) {
3665 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower ||
3666 it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3667 continue;
3668 current = it->valueRange();
3669 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) &&
3670 !qIsNaN(current.lower)) {
3671 range.lower = current.lower;
3672 haveLower = true;
3673 }
3674 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) &&
3675 !qIsNaN(current.upper)) {
3676 range.upper = current.upper;
3677 haveUpper = true;
3678 }
3679 }
3680 } else if (signDomain ==
3681 QCP::sdNegative) // range may only be in the negative sign domain
3682 {
3683 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd;
3684 ++it) {
3685 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower ||
3686 it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3687 continue;
3688 current = it->valueRange();
3689 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) && current.lower < 0 &&
3690 !qIsNaN(current.lower)) {
3691 range.lower = current.lower;
3692 haveLower = true;
3693 }
3694 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current.upper < 0 &&
3695 !qIsNaN(current.upper)) {
3696 range.upper = current.upper;
3697 haveUpper = true;
3698 }
3699 }
3700 } else if (signDomain ==
3701 QCP::sdPositive) // range may only be in the positive sign domain
3702 {
3703 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd;
3704 ++it) {
3705 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower ||
3706 it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3707 continue;
3708 current = it->valueRange();
3709 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) && current.lower > 0 &&
3710 !qIsNaN(current.lower)) {
3711 range.lower = current.lower;
3712 haveLower = true;
3713 }
3714 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current.upper > 0 &&
3715 !qIsNaN(current.upper)) {
3716 range.upper = current.upper;
3717 haveUpper = true;
3718 }
3719 }
3720 }
3721
3722 foundRange = haveLower && haveUpper;
3723 return range;
3724}
3725
3735template <class DataType>
3736void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::limitIteratorsToDataRange(
3737 const_iterator &begin, const_iterator &end,
3738 const QCPDataRange &dataRange) const {
3739 QCPDataRange iteratorRange(int(begin - constBegin()),
3740 int(end - constBegin()));
3741 iteratorRange = iteratorRange.bounded(dataRange.bounded(this->dataRange()));
3742 begin = constBegin() + iteratorRange.begin();
3743 end = constBegin() + iteratorRange.end();
3744}
3745
3756template <class DataType>
3757void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::preallocateGrow(int minimumPreallocSize) {
3758 if (minimumPreallocSize <= mPreallocSize) return;
3759
3760 int newPreallocSize = minimumPreallocSize;
3761 newPreallocSize += (1u << qBound(4, mPreallocIteration + 4, 15)) -
3762 12; // do 4 up to 32768-12 preallocation, doubling in each
3763 // intermediate iteration
3764 ++mPreallocIteration;
3765
3766 int sizeDifference = newPreallocSize - mPreallocSize;
3767 mData.resize(mData.size() + sizeDifference);
3768 std::copy_backward(mData.begin() + mPreallocSize,
3769 mData.end() - sizeDifference, mData.end());
3770 mPreallocSize = newPreallocSize;
3771}
3772
3789template <class DataType>
3790void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::performAutoSqueeze() {
3791 const int totalAlloc = mData.capacity();
3792 const int postAllocSize = totalAlloc - mData.size();
3793 const int usedSize = size();
3794 bool shrinkPostAllocation = false;
3795 bool shrinkPreAllocation = false;
3796 if (totalAlloc > 650000) // if allocation is larger, shrink earlier with
3797 // respect to total used size
3798 {
3799 shrinkPostAllocation =
3800 postAllocSize >
3801 usedSize * 1.5; // QVector grow strategy is 2^n for static data. Watch
3802 // out not to oscillate!
3803 shrinkPreAllocation = mPreallocSize * 10 > usedSize;
3804 } else if (totalAlloc >
3805 1000) // below 10 MiB raw data be generous with preallocated
3806 // memory, below 1k points don't even bother
3807 {
3808 shrinkPostAllocation = postAllocSize > usedSize * 5;
3809 shrinkPreAllocation =
3810 mPreallocSize > usedSize * 1.5; // preallocation can grow into
3811 // postallocation, so can be smaller
3812 }
3813
3814 if (shrinkPreAllocation || shrinkPostAllocation)
3815 squeeze(shrinkPreAllocation, shrinkPostAllocation);
3816}

4542// implementation of template functions:
4543
4563template <class PlottableType>
4564PlottableType *QCustomPlot::plottableAt(const QPointF &pos, bool onlySelectable,
4565 int *dataIndex) const {
4566 PlottableType *resultPlottable = 0;
4567 QVariant resultDetails;
4568 double resultDistance =
4569 mSelectionTolerance; // only regard clicks with distances smaller than
4570 // mSelectionTolerance as selections, so initialize
4571 // with that value
4572
4573 foreach (QCPAbstractPlottable *plottable, mPlottables) {
4574 PlottableType *currentPlottable = qobject_cast<PlottableType *>(plottable);
4575 if (!currentPlottable ||
4576 (onlySelectable &&
4577 !currentPlottable
4578 ->selectable())) // we could have also passed onlySelectable to
4579 // the selectTest function, but checking here is
4580 // faster, because we have access to
4581 // QCPAbstractPlottable::selectable
4582 continue;
4583 if (currentPlottable->clipRect().contains(
4584 pos.toPoint())) // only consider clicks where the plottable is
4585 // actually visible
4586 {
4587 QVariant details;
4588 double currentDistance = currentPlottable->selectTest(
4589 pos, false, dataIndex ? &details : nullptr);
4590 if (currentDistance >= 0 && currentDistance < resultDistance) {
4591 resultPlottable = currentPlottable;
4592 resultDetails = details;
4593 resultDistance = currentDistance;
4594 }
4595 }
4596 }
4597
4598 if (resultPlottable && dataIndex) {
4599 QCPDataSelection sel = resultDetails.value<QCPDataSelection>();
4600 if (!sel.isEmpty()) *dataIndex = sel.dataRange(0).begin();
4601 }
4602 return resultPlottable;
4603}
4604
4620template <class ItemType>
4621ItemType *QCustomPlot::itemAt(const QPointF &pos, bool onlySelectable) const {
4622 ItemType *resultItem = 0;
4623 double resultDistance =
4624 mSelectionTolerance; // only regard clicks with distances smaller than
4625 // mSelectionTolerance as selections, so initialize
4626 // with that value
4627
4628 foreach (QCPAbstractItem *item, mItems) {
4629 ItemType *currentItem = qobject_cast<ItemType *>(item);
4630 if (!currentItem ||
4631 (onlySelectable &&
4632 !currentItem
4633 ->selectable())) // we could have also passed onlySelectable to
4634 // the selectTest function, but checking here is
4635 // faster, because we have access to
4636 // QCPAbstractItem::selectable
4637 continue;
4638 if (!currentItem->clipToAxisRect() ||
4639 currentItem->clipRect().contains(
4640 pos.toPoint())) // only consider clicks inside axis cliprect of the
4641 // item if actually clipped to it
4642 {
4643 double currentDistance = currentItem->selectTest(pos, false);
4644 if (currentDistance >= 0 && currentDistance < resultDistance) {
4645 resultItem = currentItem;
4646 resultDistance = currentDistance;
4647 }
4648 }
4649 }
4650
4651 return resultItem;
4652}

4953template <class DataType>
4954double QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::dataMainKey(int index) const {
4955 if (index >= 0 && index < mDataContainer->size()) {
4956 return (mDataContainer->constBegin() + index)->mainKey();
4957 } else {
4958 qDebug() << Q_FUNC_INFO << "Index out of bounds" << index;
4959 return 0;
4960 }
4961}
4962
4966template <class DataType>
4967double QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::dataSortKey(int index) const {
4968 if (index >= 0 && index < mDataContainer->size()) {
4969 return (mDataContainer->constBegin() + index)->sortKey();
4970 } else {
4971 qDebug() << Q_FUNC_INFO << "Index out of bounds" << index;
4972 return 0;
4973 }

4979template <class DataType>
4980double QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::dataMainValue(int index) const {
4981 if (index >= 0 && index < mDataContainer->size()) {
4982 return (mDataContainer->constBegin() + index)->mainValue();
4983 } else {
4984 qDebug() << Q_FUNC_INFO << "Index out of bounds" << index;
4985 return 0;
4986 }
4987}
4988
4992template <class DataType>
4993QCPRange QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::dataValueRange(int index) const {
4994 if (index >= 0 && index < mDataContainer->size()) {
4995 return (mDataContainer->constBegin() + index)->valueRange();
4996 } else {
4997 qDebug() << Q_FUNC_INFO << "Index out of bounds" << index;
4998 return QCPRange(0, 0);
4999 }
5000}
5001
5005template <class DataType>
5006QPointF QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::dataPixelPosition(int index) const {
5007 if (index >= 0 && index < mDataContainer->size()) {
5008 const typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it =
5009 mDataContainer->constBegin() + index;
5010 return coordsToPixels(it->mainKey(), it->mainValue());
5011 } else {
5012 qDebug() << Q_FUNC_INFO << "Index out of bounds" << index;
5013 return QPointF();
5014 }
5015}
5016
5020template <class DataType>
5021bool QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::sortKeyIsMainKey() const {
5022 return DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey();
5023}
5024
5033template <class DataType>
5034QCPDataSelection QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::selectTestRect(
5035 const QRectF &rect, bool onlySelectable) const {
5036 QCPDataSelection result;
5037 if ((onlySelectable && mSelectable == QCP::stNone) ||
5038 mDataContainer->isEmpty())
5039 return result;
5040 if (!mKeyAxis || !mValueAxis) return result;
5041
5042 // convert rect given in pixels to ranges given in plot coordinates:
5043 double key1, value1, key2, value2;
5044 pixelsToCoords(rect.topLeft(), key1, value1);
5045 pixelsToCoords(rect.bottomRight(), key2, value2);
5046 QCPRange keyRange(key1, key2); // QCPRange normalizes internally so we don't
5047 // have to care about whether key1 < key2
5048 QCPRange valueRange(value1, value2);
5049 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator begin =
5050 mDataContainer->constBegin();
5051 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator end =
5052 mDataContainer->constEnd();
5053 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // we can assume that data is sorted by
5054 // main key, so can reduce the searched key
5055 // interval:
5056 {
5057 begin = mDataContainer->findBegin(keyRange.lower, false);
5058 end = mDataContainer->findEnd(keyRange.upper, false);
5059 }
5060 if (begin == end) return result;
5061
5062 int currentSegmentBegin =
5063 -1; // -1 means we're currently not in a segment that's contained in rect
5064 for (typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = begin;
5065 it != end; ++it) {
5066 if (currentSegmentBegin == -1) {
5067 if (valueRange.contains(it->mainValue()) &&
5068 keyRange.contains(it->mainKey())) // start segment
5069 currentSegmentBegin = int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin());
5070 } else if (!valueRange.contains(it->mainValue()) ||
5071 !keyRange.contains(it->mainKey())) // segment just ended
5072 {
5073 result.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(currentSegmentBegin,
5074 int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin())),
5075 false);
5076 currentSegmentBegin = -1;
5077 }
5078 }
5079 // process potential last segment:
5080 if (currentSegmentBegin != -1)
5081 result.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(currentSegmentBegin,
5082 int(end - mDataContainer->constBegin())),
5083 false);
5084
5085 result.simplify();
5086 return result;
5087}
5088
5092template <class DataType>
5093int QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::findBegin(double sortKey,
5094 bool expandedRange) const {
5095 return int(mDataContainer->findBegin(sortKey, expandedRange) -
5096 mDataContainer->constBegin());
5097}
5098
5102template <class DataType>
5103int QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::findEnd(double sortKey,
5104 bool expandedRange) const {
5105 return int(mDataContainer->findEnd(sortKey, expandedRange) -
5106 mDataContainer->constBegin());
5107}
5108
5120template <class DataType>
5121double QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::selectTest(const QPointF &pos,
5122 bool onlySelectable,
5123 QVariant *details) const {
5124 if ((onlySelectable && mSelectable == QCP::stNone) ||
5125 mDataContainer->isEmpty())
5126 return -1;
5127 if (!mKeyAxis || !mValueAxis) return -1;
5128
5129 QCPDataSelection selectionResult;
5130 double minDistSqr = (std::numeric_limits<double>::max)();
5131 int minDistIndex = mDataContainer->size();
5132
5133 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator begin =
5134 mDataContainer->constBegin();
5135 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator end =
5136 mDataContainer->constEnd();
5137 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // we can assume that data is sorted by
5138 // main key, so can reduce the searched key
5139 // interval:
5140 {
5141 // determine which key range comes into question, taking selection tolerance
5142 // around pos into account:
5143 double posKeyMin, posKeyMax, dummy;
5144 pixelsToCoords(pos - QPointF(mParentPlot->selectionTolerance(),
5145 mParentPlot->selectionTolerance()),
5146 posKeyMin, dummy);
5147 pixelsToCoords(pos + QPointF(mParentPlot->selectionTolerance(),
5148 mParentPlot->selectionTolerance()),
5149 posKeyMax, dummy);
5150 if (posKeyMin > posKeyMax) qSwap(posKeyMin, posKeyMax);
5151 begin = mDataContainer->findBegin(posKeyMin, true);
5152 end = mDataContainer->findEnd(posKeyMax, true);
5153 }
5154 if (begin == end) return -1;
5155 QCPRange keyRange(mKeyAxis->range());
5156 QCPRange valueRange(mValueAxis->range());
5157 for (typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = begin;
5158 it != end; ++it) {
5159 const double mainKey = it->mainKey();
5160 const double mainValue = it->mainValue();
5161 if (keyRange.contains(mainKey) &&
5162 valueRange.contains(
5163 mainValue)) // make sure data point is inside visible range, for
5164 // speedup in cases where sort key isn't main key and
5165 // we iterate over all points
5166 {
5167 const double currentDistSqr =
5168 QCPVector2D(coordsToPixels(mainKey, mainValue) - pos).lengthSquared();
5169 if (currentDistSqr < minDistSqr) {
5170 minDistSqr = currentDistSqr;
5171 minDistIndex = int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin());
5172 }
5173 }
5174 }
5175 if (minDistIndex != mDataContainer->size())
5176 selectionResult.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(minDistIndex, minDistIndex + 1),
5177 false);
5178
5179 selectionResult.simplify();
5180 if (details) details->setValue(selectionResult);
5181 return qSqrt(minDistSqr);
5182}
5183
5194template <class DataType>
5195void QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::getDataSegments(
5196 QList<QCPDataRange> &selectedSegments,
5197 QList<QCPDataRange> &unselectedSegments) const {
5198 selectedSegments.clear();
5199 unselectedSegments.clear();
5200 if (mSelectable ==
5201 QCP::stWhole) // stWhole selection type draws the entire plottable with
5202 // selected style if mSelection isn't empty
5203 {
5204 if (selected())
5205 selectedSegments << QCPDataRange(0, dataCount());
5206 else
5207 unselectedSegments << QCPDataRange(0, dataCount());
5208 } else {
5209 QCPDataSelection sel(selection());
5210 sel.simplify();
5211 selectedSegments = sel.dataRanges();
5212 unselectedSegments = sel.inverse(QCPDataRange(0, dataCount())).dataRanges();
5213 }
5214}
5215
5226template <class DataType>
5227void QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::drawPolyline(
5228 QCPPainter *painter, const QVector<QPointF> &lineData) const {
5229 // if drawing lines in plot (instead of PDF), reduce 1px lines to cosmetic,
5230 // because at least in Qt6 drawing of "1px" width lines is much slower even
5231 // though it has same appearance apart from High-DPI. In High-DPI cases people
5232 // must set a pen width slightly larger than 1.0 to get correct DPI scaling of
5233 // width, but of course with performance penalty.
5234 if (!painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmVectorized) &&
5235 qFuzzyCompare(painter->pen().widthF(), 1.0)) {
5236 QPen newPen = painter->pen();
5237 newPen.setWidth(0);
5238 painter->setPen(newPen);
5239 }
5240
5241 // if drawing solid line and not in PDF, use much faster line drawing instead
5242 // of polyline:
5243 if (mParentPlot->plottingHints().testFlag(QCP::phFastPolylines) &&
5244 painter->pen().style() == Qt::SolidLine &&
5245 !painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmVectorized) &&
5246 !painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmNoCaching)) {
5247 int i = 0;
5248 bool lastIsNan = false;
5249 const int lineDataSize = lineData.size();
5250 while (i < lineDataSize &&
5251 (qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) ||
5252 qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x()))) // make sure first point is not NaN
5253 ++i;
5254 ++i; // because drawing works in 1 point retrospect
5255 while (i < lineDataSize) {
5256 if (!qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) &&
5257 !qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x())) // NaNs create a gap in the line
5258 {
5259 if (!lastIsNan)
5260 painter->drawLine(lineData.at(i - 1), lineData.at(i));
5261 else
5262 lastIsNan = false;
5263 } else
5264 lastIsNan = true;
5265 ++i;
5266 }
5267 } else {
5268 int segmentStart = 0;
5269 int i = 0;
5270 const int lineDataSize = lineData.size();
5271 while (i < lineDataSize) {
5272 if (qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) || qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x()) ||
5273 qIsInf(
5274 lineData.at(i).y())) // NaNs create a gap in the line. Also
5275 // filter Infs which make drawPolyline block
5276 {
5277 painter->drawPolyline(
5278 lineData.constData() + segmentStart,
5279 i - segmentStart); // i, because we don't want to include the
5280 // current NaN point
5281 segmentStart = i + 1;
5282 }
5283 ++i;
5284 }
5285 // draw last segment:
5286 painter->drawPolyline(lineData.constData() + segmentStart,
5287 lineDataSize - segmentStart);
5288 }
5289}

6635class QCP_LIB_DECL QCPStatisticalBoxData {
6636 public:
6637 QCPStatisticalBoxData();
6638 QCPStatisticalBoxData(double key, double minimum, double lowerQuartile,
6639 double median, double upperQuartile, double maximum,
6640 const QVector<double> &outliers = QVector<double>());
6641
6642 inline double sortKey() const { return key; }
6643 inline static QCPStatisticalBoxData fromSortKey(double sortKey) {
6644 return QCPStatisticalBoxData(sortKey, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
6645 }
6646 inline static bool sortKeyIsMainKey() { return true; }
6647
6648 inline double mainKey() const { return key; }
6649 inline double mainValue() const { return median; }
6650
6651 inline QCPRange valueRange() const {
6652 QCPRange result(minimum, maximum);
6653 for (QVector<double>::const_iterator it = outliers.constBegin();
6654 it != outliers.constEnd(); ++it)
6655 result.expand(*it);
6656 return result;
6657 }
6658
6659 double key, minimum, lowerQuartile, median, upperQuartile, maximum;
6660 QVector<double> outliers;
6661};

8323 void moveRange(double diff);
8324 void scaleRange(double factor);
8325 void scaleRange(double factor, double center);
8326 void rescale(bool onlyVisiblePlottables = false);
8327 double coordToAngleRad(double coord) const {
8328 return mAngleRad + (coord - mRange.lower) / mRange.size() *
8329 (mRangeReversed ? -2.0 * M_PI : 2.0 * M_PI);
8330 } // mention in doc that return doesn't wrap
8331 double angleRadToCoord(double angleRad) const {
8332 return mRange.lower + (angleRad - mAngleRad) /
8333 (mRangeReversed ? -2.0 * M_PI : 2.0 * M_PI) *
8334 mRange.size();
8335 }

8337 double &radiusCoord) const;
